{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632146","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632146"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:36:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:36:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17420"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17420","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17420"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10110"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70559"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10110","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10110"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17420"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56023"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5501"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23683"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23687"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70559","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70559"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ESocial marketing is increasingly used in public health to promote positive health behaviours. This approach applies commercial marketing principles to achieve social good rather than financial profit.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the core principle of social marketing in healthcare?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Focusing solely on mass media campaigns","Promoting only government health services","Using fear-based messaging exclusively","Exchange of value between program and audience","Maximising financial returns from health programs"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe core principle of social marketing is the \u003Cstrong\u003Eexchange of value between program and audience\u003C/strong\u003E. This means understanding what the target audience values and creating programs that offer clear benefits in exchange for adopting healthy behaviours.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFocusing solely on mass media campaigns\u003C/strong\u003E - Social marketing requires a comprehensive approach using multiple channels and strategies to reach target audiences effectively.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPromoting only government health services\u003C/strong\u003E - Social marketing principles can be applied by any organisation seeking to promote positive health behaviours, including non-government and community organisations.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EUsing fear-based messaging exclusively\u003C/strong\u003E - Effective social marketing employs a range of messaging strategies including positive motivation, social norms, and enablement, not just fear appeals.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMaximising financial returns from health programs\u003C/strong\u003E - The primary goal of social marketing is to achieve positive social and health outcomes rather than generate financial profit.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESuccessful social marketing campaigns apply commercial marketing principles including audience segmentation, competitive analysis, and the marketing mix (4 P\u0027s: Product, Price, Place, Promotion) to influence health behaviours.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Social marketing in healthcare applies commercial marketing principles to promote beneficial health behaviours and social good.","The 4 P\u0027s of marketing (Product, Price, Place, Promotion) are fundamental principles used in health promotion campaigns.","Effective health marketing requires understanding target audience needs, barriers, and motivations."],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56023"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17420"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56023","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56023"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-15T19:17:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-04T00:09:26+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10110"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70559"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"dat